OL,6,FAdvocate Heywood added that Macleod
OL,7,Fwould have access to counselling
OL,8,Fservices through the company,
OL,9,Fsomething he denied.
OL,11,FMacleod alleged "the society cut off
OL,12,Fall funding for psychiatric treatment"
OL,13,Fand as a result, his appointments were
OL,14,Fcancelled.
OL,16,FAdvocate Heywood disputed this claim,
OL,17,Fwith evidence from medical
OL,18,Fprofessionals and psychologists read
OL,19,Fout in court saying Macleod "appeared
OL,20,Fmotivated to return to work" and was
OL,21,F"expected to make a full recovery".
